caption: Great sandwiches, salads, soups, and pizza!
The food is good and affordable for a quick bite. The staff is formed of grumpy old men though 😂

Jim and the crew do a great job. The food here is always delicious, and they have so many options. The daily specials are a big hit as well. Italian Beef Friday's, Buffalo Wing Pizza, Milano and Roma are a few favs!
The staffs are so slow and rude . But the place was good. Prices are comparable with good service.
Chicago breakfast layover to the Minneapolis. Fat n happy for four hours. Thanks
Could of added another meetball to sandwich

This spot is the bomb! Their food is consistently delicious.  Staff could be a bit more friendlier, but they are very attentive to their tables and their values during COVID are exceptional. They don't play music as they have a jukebox no one ever uses.  Perhaps their only improvement is to play some tunes authentic to their Hispanic culture
I can not say enough good stuff about this place they are great!!!
As of 6/2, Arturo's has reopened.  Great food, service and people.  Support this and other family businesses.
One of my preferred places to grab something to eat. awesome location, well organised, and very good service. Keep it up!
The "go-to" place for Italian lunch.  Panini, pasta, salads.
Great Staff; very professional; great food and lots of smiles...we love Jimmy too! Renay & Janeann
Love the pizza and the staff is very friendly!
A great value.. a good choice for a quick lunch at a reasonable price.
Whatever you need, whenever you need it - deliciously fresh and delivered with a smile. Price / quantity relation is unbeatable! Thanks for taking care of my team, they looooove you guys!!
Good price
Lamb neck was amazing

Food is delicious! Great customer service and owner is super friendly!!  I typically go here for lunch during the week and get a variety of their salads and sandwiches. Will continue to be a “go-to” during the work week
Good food, fast and friendly service, healthy portions, reasonable price.  Perfect spot for a quick lunch!
Great food at a good price
Great food, friendly staff, exceptional specials.  Update: still amazing, the Italian Beef is out of this world.
Fast service, great food, extensive option for sandwiches, pizzas, paninis, pastas and some options for breakfast. A must if you are in the area.
Loved the panini. It had good amount of cheese with a little kick of spicy-ness and the bread was grilled perfectly.
lovely place to stop by for lunch, staff care about making sure you have a good time
Great daily lunch specials!
Great daily food specials, very fairly priced, and good tasting food and in my cookbook this is a perfect recipe.
Good food with great lunch prices
Really cool restaurant The food is top notch and well prepared. Great music selection. The wait staff was amazing. Would definitely go back when I'm in the area.
Staff is great. Always accommodating to last minute catering orders. They are always willing to go the extra mile.
Best breakfast sandwiches in the loop
Cheap, fast, and good sandwiches!
Always good food and great daily specials (weekdays). Check out their menu!
The chicken ceaser salad is so delicious I can eat it everyday
Great for cold and hot sandwiches friendly staff.

It's a nice little place with a wide selection of foods,  they have sandwiches,  salads, pastas, pizza and probably other stuff that I don't know of. They have a daily special that comes with an entree and a drink for $6, that's a price you can't beat in the west loop. The place gets really crowded around lunch time but the staff has always been nice and tries to get you in and out, sometimes they move too fast, my pasta ends up with too much water on the bottom.  I also take my lunch to go because it's a small place and it gets very loud.
italian food at this spot - delicious. Looking forward to a return trip. Prices were reasonable.

I work at a non-profit in the area and order from Arturo's all the time for corporate lunches.  1. Everyone loves the food. Ordering for a group of people is always tough because people are particular in what they like and Arturo's is the only place I have ordered from where I never receive any complaints.  2. The service is incredible. I know I can always rely on them and they are so professional.  Whenever anyone asks me for recommendations on where to order from in the area, Arturo's is always at the top of the list. Thanks for being so great!
There are three of us. We all got sandwiches. These are probably the best sandwiches any of us have ever had. This place is amazing and you should definitely give it a try.
Amazing prices for good food. Small and cute place for a lunch with friends
Very good decent price for downtown

Very friendly! I had the pepper egg sandwich meal - the bread was fresh and warm and price was super reasonable. Many different options from soup, salad, sandwiches and pizza. Plenty of seating as well.
Good food at a great price.  The daily specials are an even better deal. The owner is a good person and generally cares about your experience.
Go for the Friday special! Great sandwiches, great service and customers are super loyal, helped me out with my choices :) people apparently come here every Friday for the special!
The food was excellent! Italian beef was wonderful! Staff was fun and engaging! Great first stop in Chicago!!!
Best sandwiches for breakfast and lunch! Check out their daily specials!
The best "chicken pesto" sandwich in Chicago !

This place is amazing. My fiancé and I are Chicago natives, and moved to Kentucky a few years ago... one problem.... there’s no place like sweet home Chicago for food. Anytime my family visits us, we beg them to bring us what they can so we can revel in our pastimes. My mom went here and asked them for a special order so she can pack it up and bring it to us on her visit this past week. It was AMAZING! Thank you so much for helping her and even walking the food over to her building downtown while she was at work. Your kindness and generosity moves mountains. We thoroughly enjoyed our wonderful sandwiches down here in Kentucky with our family!

Fantastic food and service. Walked in here for my first time and it was apparent I didn't know what to do or what I wanted.They treated me like I was their best customer, gave me suggestions on what to order and served it fast and delicious. I will definitely come back
First visit and the salad was delicious
Quick, cafeteria style Italian food. They lose points for not having vegan options, besides a salad.
Nice place for quick bite and full meal. I had veg Pizza and it's quite good.
Friendliest place to get lunch, has great specials and  the Italian sub beats the other local sandwich places hands down. Oh and best Italian beef I've ever had.
Great food,  quick service
Amazing sandwich.  Fast and friendly staff.

The pesto chicken sandwich with hot sauce is one of the best sandwiches I've had in Chicago. Great place with a huge menu and very friendly staff. They stand out amid the saturated market of Italian lunch spots in the city.
Clean fast really good food
Good food, been visiting for years.
Everything on the menu is good, especially the daily special.
If you need a quick bite to eat, this is the place to go. They have really good sandwiches/pasta/pizza here. Customer service here is amazing!
Impromptu visit, big big hit. Spinach lasagna worth coming back for!
The staff and the sandwiches are great.
Incredibly friendly staff and wonderful food. A awesome place to get lunch!
Love this place! I always eat there when I'm downtown in that area! Fairly priced and great tasting food!

This is my absolute favorite lunch spot downtown. I moved jobs across the loop and I still frequently make the trip over just for Arturo's Chicken Pesto Panini. I have yet to find anything as good. Quick service, a lot of variety. And a great staff.
Excellent choice is Italian food
Good food!
absolutely amazing every time i go. Get the Frank's Special for breakfast... hidden gem.
Fresh and good food
Great food, relatively inexpensive. Great workers as well.
Everything is good here!  You can't beat the value of their daily lunch special.
Best Italian beef I've had so far.
Great sandwiches. Really great staff.
Super friendly employees, owner usually on-site working with everyone, excellent food options, daily meal deals are great! Pizza with a smile, if you're lucky.
If you've been to Fantanos on Michigan and Van Buren, then you'll love this place. I call it Fontanos 2.0
Great local Chicago eatery wirh good service.
I love this place! From their breakfast sandwiches through chili, pasta, hot subs, pizza, and the irresistible pesto chicken sandwich, Arturo's doesn't disappoint!
Good fast eats
Great food and fast service. Daily specials. The soup is always good.

Arturo’s is my favorite spot for lunch. Always great food, excellent prices and an even better staff. At Arturo’s, I can relax and zone out for the lunch hour. There’s not many places downtown that can offer that effect. Try the Italian beef, Mac n cheese, pizza or any of the sandwiches, you won’t be disappointed.
Amazing Service, great food at very reasonable prices. The Staff is Super friendly

Before working in a near by building, found myself here for some good eats. The menu selection was the first thing that stood out to me. Next was the amazing staff and delicous aforementioned food :). All these reasons are why I keep coming!
Friendly staff with a variety of Italian options
Daily deals under  $8
Great daily specials!
Great Italian Beefs
Great lunch specials
It looks to me like they might have some pretty good food everybody talks about it it's right next door to where I work I'm going to try it one day this week I'll try it
Great food, great value, very fast service!!
Good food, great service and good daily specials.
Delicious food nice and quick!  The daily specials ($6.00) are such a steal for lunch in Chicago.  Friday's Italian Beef special is a hard deal to beat.
Get the special any day, great food. Let's Go Rangers!
Standard quick loop lunch spot specializing in Italian sandwiches, pizza and salads. Decent specials for each day but the food doesn't blow your mind.
Check their menu for good daily deals. Friday is a good Italian beef combo deal. This is a good once a month spot.
I had the Italian beef combo and it was amazing. My wife had Genoa sub and was very satisfied. Service was fast and with a smile. Great food

Terrific for grab and go, especially breakfast sammies and a cappuccino. I've had their salads, good. The hot food bar is tempting - I'll check it out when I've got more than ten minutes to spare. Really nice people.
Great Italian food with daily specials
Great place and staff was great. They help me navigate through the city! Had the Genoa Italian Sub, one word.....Awesome!!!

Our office uses Arturo Express to cater some of our lunch meetings.  I generally try to offer super healthy food, low sodium, low cholesterol, organic ingredients.  That is not Arturo Express's specialty. Arturo Express serves GREAT COMFORT Food!!!  Plenty of options to make everyone happy,  from vegetarians, gluten frees and meat eaters.
Especially love the pasta and yummy home made sauces. You can't beat it for value.
The restaurant serves freshly prepared foods at fair prices.
Great food, staff and price. Great for work lunch with coworkers or on your own
Great food and fantastic service! Arturo Express is my favorite lunch spot in the loop!

Arturo's is a nice break from the swarm of chain restaurants that envelop the loop. Even if there is a long line, it moves very quickly. My favorite options are the pasta specials and the Italian beef. Friendly staff and reasonable prices.
Fast and tasty lunch spot. Ordered the California Hot sandwich.

I found this place through one of my coworkers and am so glad I did. Arturo Express is a great place to grab a quick breakfast to bring into work and also an amazing spot for a quick and affordable lunch.  All of their breakfast sandwiches taste great!  I have to warn you though if you are going here for lunch and plan to sit down you'd better get here early. The spots fill up quick and with their amazingly tasty $6 lunch specials it's clear on why. I really can't stress enough to get here early or a bit late if you hate lines though ;) The food makes it worth it but if you are in a hurry for lunch you'll be a little annoyed.  The Italian Beef might not be Al's but it's still really good and all of the sandwiches (specially the Genoa) are delicious. The pizza is a winner and I hear the pasta is pretty good too though usually it's not what I'm in the mood for at lunch so haven't tried it yet.  Great staff that's always friendly and helps the line move as quickly as possible who are all happy to help with a smile on their face.

I’ve worked in the Loop for over 4 years now and Arturo’s has become one of my favorite lunch spots.  In a world where $10 Corner Bakery lunches are the norm, Arturo’s $6 lunch specials are a breath of fresh air.  I usually stop in on Fridays for the $6 Italian beef special with chips and a drink.  I’ve had a few of the other salads and sandwiches and they were all great.  The line can get long during prime lunch time, but the Arturo’s staff is efficient and friendly.
Breakfast bagel sandwich are GREAT!
